column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Partly cloudy day.  Slight wave action.  Air temp. 80 F.  Bladderwort less evident.
Bladder wort on bottom- came up with disk
Very windy last few days.  Today is calm.  Decaying bladder wort came up with disk.
Slight breeze.  Lake level about 12" below normal.  air temp is 50
Wind out of the west.  Clear skies.  Air temp 59. Saw two loons.
Wind out of the north.  Saw a loon and an eagle.
Calm.  Air temp 75.  Beautiful day.  No bladderwart yet.
Hazy to partly cloudy.  Wind out of NW- cool.  Air temp 68-70.  Accompanied by Tom Radke and Wynn Jones.
Breeze out of the south.  Air temp 82.  Water surface temp 75.
Partly cloudy and calm.  Air temp about 85.  Small amounts of bladder wart appearing.  Accompanied by Lou Wilhelm (we used Lou's boat).
Beautiful day.  Air temp about 80.  Some bladderwort but not nearly as much as last year.  Accompanied by Linda Boyd
Slightly hazy.  Air temp about 80.  Less bladderwort than two weeks ago.  Accompanied by Linda Boyd.  Great Blue Heron in the channel to Flannery Lake.
Gorgeous day on Velvet Lake.  Calm winds- air temp about 70.  A little bladderwart floating but most of it is at the bottom.  Accompanied by Emily Boyd.
Foggy earlier- clearing as we launched.  Air temp about 55.  Accompanied by Linda Boyd and Brad and Patty Erickson.
Hazy-slight breeze from the south. Air temp 45.  Accompanied by Linda Boyd

Beautiful day.  Calm winds.  Air temp about 55 degrees.  Accompanied by Bob Friday with me on Lou Wilhelms pontoon boat and JR Barttelt in the boat with representatives from Northern Environment- who will be doing the lake study for the Lake Association
79 degrees.  Full sun-  slight wind out of the NW
85 degrees.  Partly cloudy- slight wind out of the NW
72 degrees.  Strong wind out of the S
Air temp 59.  Light wind out of the southwest
Southwest wind light.  Air temp 74.  Partly cloudy.
Clear skies.  Wind out of the west.  Lots of bladder wart.  Water is murkier than I have ever seen it.  Air temp 75
Bladder wort mostly gone.  Wind light out of the south.  Beautiful day.
Air temperature 70 Degrees.  West wind light.
Air temp 59 degrees!  No bladder wort yet.  Water level very low.
Partly cloudy- air temp 78 degrees.  Loon nesting on large island near deep hole.  Lots of pollen on surface of water- no bladder wort yet.
Air temp 63 degrees.  Some bladder wort.  Had to stop twice to remove bladder wort from motor.  Lake level still lower than last time.
Air temp about 77.  Winds light out of the south.  Beautiful day on the lake.
Beautiful day.  Hazy sunshine.  Air temp 70 degrees.
Air temp 60.  Light south winds.  Three loons on Flannery Lake
Light winds out of the east.  Air Temp about 70
Air temp 72.  Light variable winds.  Clear Skies
Air temp about 67.  Accompanied by Linda Boyd.  Light winds.
Clear skies.  Air temp about 69 degrees
Air temp 70 degrees.  Light winds. A beautiful day.  No bladder wart yet
Air temp 83.  Clear skies and light winds.
Air temp 84.  Clear skies and light winds.
Air temp 77.  Winds light out of the south.  Another great day!
Air temp 71.  Winds light out of the northwest.  Clear skies.
Air temp 72.  Winds from the northwest.  Partly cloudy
Air temp 75.  Partly cloudy.  Winds out of the south.  Loons nesting on Flannery
Bright sunny day.  Air temp 79.  Surface water temp 80.  Loons abandoned nest July 5.
Cool.  Temp 62.  Winds out of the north.  Partly cloudy
Air remp 60.  Winds from the south at 15mph.  Water stirred up from the wind.
Clear skies- Air temp 70 degrees.Wind out of the north.  Moderate amount of Purple Bladder Wort on surface.
Surface water temperature 66 degrees.  Air temp 72 .  Partly cloudy.
Partly cloudy.  Air temp 75.  Accompanied by Linda Boyd.  Eagles high overhead.
Warm- 84 degrees.  Winds light and variable.  Moderate amount of large purple bladderwort has surfaced.
Air temp about 65.  Winds out of the northwest about 10.
Air temp is 75.  Water is a bit stirred up.
Accompanied by Emily and Veda Murthy.  Light winds out of the north to northwest.   No bladder wort seen in Velvet Lake.
We did not have the DO meter with us (another lake association was using it today)- so we did not take readings.
Cool and clear.  Bright sunshine.  Using Rod Linder's boat and accompanied by Rod and his dogs Hutch and Zeke.  Two loons in Velvet Lake.
Partly cloudy- air temp 74-  One loon in Velvet
Accompanied by Linda Boyd.  Air temp 60.  Very small amounts of Bladderwort.
Clear weather- wind light from the west.
Moderate bladderwort.  Skies clear air temp 63
